.TH "amdgpu_bo_get_metadata" 9 "amdgpu_bo_get_metadata" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_bo_get_metadata \- get metadata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" amdgpu_bo_get_metadata
.BI "(struct amdgpu_bo *bo "  ","
.BI "void *buffer "  ","
.BI "size_t buffer_size "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *metadata_size "  ","
.BI "uint64_t *flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bo" 12
\fIamdgpu_bo\fP buffer object
.IP "buffer" 12
returned metadata
.IP "buffer_size" 12
size of the buffer
.IP "metadata_size" 12
size of the returned metadata
.IP "flags" 12
flags of the returned metadata
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets buffer object's metadata, its size and flags. buffer_size shall not be
less than metadata_size.
Used via GEM ioctl.
.SH "RETURN"
0 for success or a negative error code on failure.
